Subject: Re: [T2] Oil dipstick tube seal and fan shroud flaps

On Sat, 18 Jul 2009, Monty Rowden wrote:

> Hi, I'm Monty and I have a 1974 Westy.  I'm currently rebuilding the engine
> and I put on the fan shroud and noticed that the back end of the dipstick tube
> does not go in to the oil filler neck portion.  There is approximately a
> half-inch gap inbetween the two.  Is there a seal that is supposed to go
> inbetween there or do i need to tap the dipstick tube down into the oil filler
> neck pipe.

there is a small rubber boot that fits between the two, very hard to
find but many have found that a spark plug boot will often work, might
have to pick and chose one that works
 >
> Also, there are two air vents that don't have the flaps at the bottom of the
> fan shroud. There are the holes where hinges are supposed to be I guess.  Do I
> need the flaps?  Any help would be appreciated thank you.

yes there are two hinged flaps that fit there, these push air thru the
heat system.  if you cannot get them hooked up do not leave open as
the engine may not cool properly.  cover them with something that will
seal.  many ways to do this.


good luck
Bob



